      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable that advice to \"stay positive\" feels dismissive when you are facing an unbearable reality like chronic nerve pain; your feelings of hopelessness are valid and you deserve to be heard without judging yourself. Many people with chronic pain face similar feelings of futility, and connecting specifically with pain advocates or support groups shared only by those who understand the physical toll can sometimes feel less generic than medical advice. Please consider reaching out to online communities moderated by fellow patients for moments of human connection that acknowledge your struggle, as simply knowing others have survived this specific barrier can be a lifeline.",
