      "content": "it's just that even with the groups, the conversation is always about how to survive the next day. but what if i don't want to survive it? what if i just want it to be over? i've been thinking a lot about the idea of mercy. if there was a way to just... quietly exit, to stop the noise and the burning, would that really be a bad thing? would it be wrong to want to choose peace instead of this endless agony?",
